Write a method that takes an array of strings and returns an array which has 1) each of the strings reversed, and 2) the order of the strings in the array reversed. 
For example, if the input is [“horse”, “cowboy”, “yeehaw”], the method should return [“waheey”, “yobwoc”, “esroh”].
Hint: you may want to write a helper method which just manages the task of reversing a single string.



class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {

    String[] strArr = {"horse", "cowboy", "yeehaw"};
    String[] reverseStrArr = reverseArr(strArr);
    for(int i = 0; i < reverseStrArr.length; i++) {
      System.out.println(reverseStrArr[i]);
    }

  }

  public static String[] reverseArr(String[] a) {

    String[] newA = new String[a.length];
    for(int i = 0; i < a.length; i++) {
      newA[a.length-1-i] = reverseStr(a[i]);
    }
    return newA;

  }

  public static String reverseStr(String s) {

    String newS = "";
    for(int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
      newS = s.charAt(i) + newS;
    }
    return newS;

  }
}
